<div class="page" id="page3">
      <p>
        Temperature is measured in degrees <b>Celsius</b> or <b>Fahrenheit</b>. In the United States, we mostly
        use Fahrenheit. But in science (and most of the rest of the world), the standard unit is Celsius.
      </p>
      <p>
        In Fahrenheit, water freezes at 32 degrees and boils at 212 degress.
      </p>
      <p>
        But in Celcius, water freezes at 0 degrees and boils at 100 degrees. (This is pretty easy to remember, right?)
      </p>
      <p>
        The Fahrenheit and Celcius scales in the range of water freezing and boiling are shown on a number line below:
      </p>

